40|$|This study {{uses the}} theory of logics to answer the question: What are the effects of cash-for-care on the professionalism of formal care workers in home care? Interviews with <b>home</b> <b>helps</b> on the {{influence}} of cash-for-care on three salient dimensions of professionalism (autonomy, discretionary space and professional norms) show that there is little tangible effect, but there are differences in the way <b>home</b> <b>helps</b> think. The reason why cash-for-care has so little effect on the professionalism of <b>home</b> <b>helps</b> must be sought in bureaucratic logic: it prevents the market logic of cash-for-care to have any effect on professionalism...|$|R
