50|$|Programmes for Students of Assumption Pathway School: Temasek Cares {{partnered with}} the Assumption Pathway School (APS) to award {{education}} bursaries to APS students from low-income families {{to help them}} with educational-related expenses. Temasek Cares also funds a programme to provide a family social worker to assist students from dysfunctional families. Under this programme, the family social worker will visit the students in their <b>homes</b> to <b>help</b> them overcome challenges which affect their emotional well-being and attendance at school. They support the school’s existing counsellors and teachers, who focus on the academic, social, and emotional needs of the student. The family social workers assess the needs of the family, provide counselling, direct the family to available <b>help</b> <b>schemes</b> and programmes, and follow up on progress made. Learning support specialists, such as a literacy coach and an educational psychologist, help students with learning needs to better access the curriculum.|$|R
